{"title":"On Continual Model Refinement in Out-of-Distribution Data Streams","domain":"LLM_NLP","seeds":[{"problem":"Deployed NLP models face boundary-agnostic, non-stationary OOD data streams and must be continually refined from their own prediction errors without catastrophic forgetting, while maintaining upstream/online knowledge and generalizing to unseen data.","method":"Introduce the Continual Model Refinement (CMR) formulation that operates on error streams Et extracted from incoming queries Qt (mis-predictions by the current model). Provide a comprehensive evaluation protocol with five metrics—instant Error-Fixing Rate (EFR), Upstream/Online Knowledge Retention (UKR/OKR), Cumulative Success Rate (CSR), and Knowledge Generalization (KG)—and an overall criterion (OEC). Propose a general sampling algorithm to generate dynamic OOD query streams: at each episode, sample from (i) in-distribution V0 with a decaying proportion controlled by α, (ii) a major OOD cluster Vc_t chosen via a Markov chain with transition probability β, and (iii) remaining OOD clusters to ensure diversity controlled by γ; use multiple validation/testing streams for robust benchmarking."},{"problem":"How to practically refine NLP models online on error-centric OOD streams while mitigating forgetting and preserving generalization in the CMR setting.","method":"Adapt and extend continual learning methods to CMR. For regularization, use Online L2 parameter penalty and Online EWC with an efficient running sum of Fisher information to constrain parameter drift. For replay, employ Experience Replay and conditional replay with two CMR-specific design choices: (i) Bi-Memory that separates upstream memory Mu=D from a growing online memory Mo built from Et, and (ii) Mixed-Tuning that jointly fine-tunes on Rt and Et. Propose MaxLoss, a variant of MIR that ranks replay candidates by the virtual model’s loss loss(ˆft(x),y) rather than the loss delta. Empirically, replay improves both OKR and UKR over pure regularization, Online EWC attains the strongest KG on held-out OOD data, MaxLoss yields more stable/high OKR(T) than MIR as buffer size grows, and combining MIR with Online L2Reg further boosts overall OEC(T)."}]}
